Setup for openwrt on TP-Link MR3040 as a dugnadsnett.no mesh node
=================================================================

First, install openwrt on the machine using the recipe available from 
<URL: http://wiki.openwrt.org/toh/tp-link/tl-mr3040 >.

Then, install the kmod-batman-adv package using "opkg install kmod-batman-adv".

Next, copy the provided files network, wireless and batman-adv into
/etc/config/ in the openwrt installation.

Reboot openwrt to get a working mesh node.
